                </div>
                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h3 class="subheading">4. Performance and Engine Options</h3>
                <p>Under the hood, the Kia Syros offers multiple engine options to cater to varied driving preferences. The base variant comes with a 1.5L petrol engine, while the higher trims offer a 1.4L turbocharged petrol and a 1.6L diesel engine. Both manual and automatic transmission options are available, ensuring a seamless driving experience. The Syros also includes driving modes such as Eco, Sport, and Comfort to adapt to different terrains and conditions.</p>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center"><img src="~/images/blogs/2024/theallnewkiasyrosacomprehensivereview/performance and engine options.webp" alt="Performance and Engine Options" title="Performance and Engine Options" /></div>
                </div>
                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h3 class="subheading">5. Safety and Technology</h3>
                <p>Safety is a top priority for Kia, and the Syros is no exception. It is equipped with advanced safety features like:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Six airbags</li>
                    <li>ABS with EBD</li>
                    <li>Lane Keep Assist</li>
                    <li>Blind Spot Monitoring</li>
                    <li>360-degree camera</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Additionally, the Syros incorporates cutting-edge technology, including a voice command system, adaptive cruise control, and over-the-air software updates.</p>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-4 text-center"><img src="~/images/blogs/2024/theallnewkiasyrosacomprehensivereview/safety and technology1.webp" alt="Safety and Technology1" title="Safety and Technology1" /></div>
